      "content": "In the context of this clause, the concept of sheer chaos or unpredictability may not be sufficient to qualify as an unforeseeable circumstance. Courts and contract law generally require a demonstration of contingency or extraordinary nature to an event, rather than just a simple breakdown or unexpected failure. To be considered unforeseeable, the event must be unusually unusual or incapable of being anticipated, rather than simply a natural part of a complex system. If the random interruptions appear chaotic, but still follow underlying logical patterns or precursor conditions, it might not be deemed unforeseeable.",
